    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA269-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu tōḻi vāyiṉ maṟuttatu. 2. celavu aḻuṅkivittatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is how the confidante refused mediation/the door. 2. What prevents going.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA269">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            kurumpai maṇippūṭ peruñceṅ kiṇkiṇip</l>
<l>            pālār tuvarvāyp paimpūð putalvaṉ</l>
<l>            mālaik kaṭṭiṉ mārpūr piḻiya</l>
<l>            vavveyi ṟoḻukiya vavvāy māṇakaic</l>
<l>            ceyirtīr koḷkainam muyirveṅ kātali </l>
<l>            tirumukat talamvaruṅ kaṇṇiṉain talkalum</l>
<l>            perumara vaḷḷiyiṟ piṇikku meṉṉā</l>
<l>            ciṟupal kuṉṟa miṟappō</l>
<l>            raṟivār yāravar muṉṉi yavvē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The one who traverses many small hills</l>
<l rend="indent">without saying</l>
<l rend="indent">“she fetters<note place="foot">Here syntax is very awkwardly twisted, but I suggest to read <term xml:lang="ta">kātali</term> as subject to <term xml:lang="ta">piṇikkum</term>, while the <term xml:lang="ta">niṉaintu</term> clause has to be taken as a kind of parenthesis.</note> [me] like a creeper a big tree,”</l>
<l rend="indent2">all night thinking of the eyes, moving agitatedly in the brilliant face,</l>
<l rend="indent">“[our] hotly beloved, our life, with faultless principles,</l>
<l rend="indent">a glorious smile on that mouth on which flowed [saliva] from those teeth,</l>
<l rend="indent2">while the son with green ornaments [and] a coral mouth feeding on milk,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with big red tinkling anklets [and] ornaments with unripe coconut-</l>
<l rend="indent2">kernels for gems, ascends [and] descends on [her] sweet chest tied</l>
<l rend="indent2">with garlands,”</l>
<l>– who knows what he is about?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
